  "texts": [
    "The domain of NLP has seen a remarkable transformation in recent years, primarily driven by the introduction of LLMs 1.",
    "Transformer-based Language Models (TLMs) initially led about a revolution by showing outstanding capabilities in capturing extensive dependencies 2.",
    "However, the challenges connected with adapting TLMs to various tasks, combined with their resource-intensive training, resulted to the development of more powerful models, such as GPT-3 3.",
    "With billions of parameters, these LLMs have not only boosted performance benchmarks across various tasks but have also extended their applications into novel domains, including creative writing and multimodal learning 4.",
    "Despite their notable achievements, a in-depth analysis of LLMs reveals several major limitations."
  ],
